The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 December is 10,749 (1,244.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 December, there were 823 new confirmed cases (95.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 December, there were 516 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 59% (307 extra cases).
